  "text": "The meaning of the inequality (3) is that there exists at least one node i in the set S with pa G (i) ∩ S = ∅. In other words, the induced subgraph G S has at least one initial node, that is, a node i ∈ S with no j ∈ S such that j → i in G S . Because G S is an acyclic directed graph over S , the existence of such a node i ∈ S is obvious. That is why (3) holds for every acyclic directed graph G. Recently, we have established the relation of the characteristic imset to this straightforward code of G [CITATION_1] . Actually, c G is a linear function of η G given by",
